body:
@exceptionfactory : So i think there's an issue with the conditional mode approach which i'd overlooked when you suggested it. The core of this issue is that `MergeContent` cannot handle when _any single tar entry_ is larger than 8.5GB. It has no issue creating tar archives which end up being larger than 8.5GB in total. The output mode needs to be set on the entire tar archive, so i feel this is an all or nothing thing.

Perhaps we could compute whether any one tar entry (e.g. FlowFile) is larger than 8.5GB and if that's the case then we set the `bigNumberMode()` and otherwise leave the implementation as is. I believe the only other alternative is to add a processor property to have it always/never set the `bigNumberMode()`.

Thoughts?
